---
import "../styles/about.css";
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import Icon from "../components/icons/Icon.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About — Samuel Reichert"
  description="Senior Frontend Engineer. React Native developer. Lover of travel, books, investing, and fitness."
  path="/about"
>
  <section class="page-hero about-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <span class="eyebrow reveal-eager">About</span>
      <h1 class="reveal-eager">
        A frontend engineer<br />
        <span class="it">with a long-term thesis.</span>
      </h1>
      <p class="lede reveal-eager">
        I'm Samuel — a Senior Frontend Engineer based in Rotterdam. I build for
        the web, love what React Native is becoming, and treat every interface
        as a small piece of writing.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section-flush">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="about-split">
        <figure class="portrait reveal">
          <div class="frame-corner fc-tl"></div>
          <div class="frame-corner fc-tr"></div>
          <div class="frame-corner fc-bl"></div>
          <div class="frame-corner fc-br"></div>
          <span class="monogram">SR</span>
          <div class="caption">— Samuel Reichert · MMXXVI —</div>
        </figure>

        <div class="about-text">
          <div class="reveal reveal-delay-80">
            <span class="eyebrow">The work</span>
            <h2>
              Crafting interfaces that<br />
              <span class="it">feel inevitable.</span>
            </h2>
            <p>
              For over a decade I've shipped products in React, TypeScript and
              the half-dozen tools that orbit them. The titles changed —
              engineer, lead, senior — but the obsession didn't: how a screen
              feels when you reach for it, how typography breathes at every
              breakpoint, how a click can feel like a decision instead of a
              step.
            </p>
            <p>
              React Native pulled me back into the mobile world. There's
              something honest about a phone in the hand — no clever pointer
              states, no excuses. Just motion, weight, and intent.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="reveal reveal-delay-160">
            <p class="pull">
              Good software, like good tailoring, hides its seams. The user
              shouldn't notice the work — only feel that they're in capable
              hands.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="reveal reveal-delay-200">
            <span class="eyebrow">The person</span>
            <h2>
              More than a <span class="it">developer.</span>
            </h2>
            <p>
              Outside the editor I travel — slowly, when I can. I read across
              genres (high fantasy on Sundays, Buffett's letters on Mondays). I
              treat investing as a long game and the gym as my daily reset. The
              thread that ties it all together is the same thing I look for in
              code: a pursuit of compounding returns.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section interests">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-head reveal">
        <span class="eyebrow">Off the clock</span>
        <h2>The four pillars <span class="it">that keep me sharp.</span></h2>
      </div>

      <div class="interests-grid">
        <div class="lux-card interest reveal reveal-delay-60">
          <span class="num">— 01</span>
          <div class="ic">✈</div>
          <div>
            <h3>Travel</h3>
            <p class="body">
              Explorer of the world — from canal cities to mountain villages, I
              collect places the way some collect books.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="lux-card interest reveal reveal-delay-140">
          <span class="num">— 02</span>
          <div class="ic">◈</div>
          <div>
            <h3>Investing</h3>
            <p class="body">
              Equities, FIIs, ETFs and Fixed Income — patiently building my own
              path to financial freedom.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="lux-card interest reveal reveal-delay-220">
          <span class="num">— 03</span>
          <div class="ic">❦</div>
          <div>
            <h3>Reading</h3>
            <p class="body">
              From fantasy to finance — always learning, always taking notes in
              the margins.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="lux-card interest reveal reveal-delay-300">
          <span class="num">— 04</span>
          <div class="ic">⟁</div>
          <div>
            <h3>Fitness</h3>
            <p class="body">
              The gym is my daily reset — discipline that quietly underwrites
              everything else.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section-flush">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="closing reveal">
        <div class="quote-mark">"</div>
        <div class="closing-text">
          The aim is simple — <span class="gold">freedom</span>.<br />
          The means is patience, code, and compounding.
        </div>
        <div class="sig">— Long-term plan · Always shipping —</div>
      </div>

      <section class="journey-next reveal" aria-labelledby="about-next">
        <div>
          <span class="eyebrow">Next step</span>
          <h2 id="about-next">
            Start the
            <span class="it">conversation.</span>
          </h2>
          <p>
            If the work, experience, and values line up with what you are
            building, the contact page is the cleanest next move.
          </p>
        </div>
        <a class="btn btn-primary" href="/contact">
          Contact Me
          <Icon name="arrow-right" class="arrow" size={14} />
        </a>
      </section>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
